# Wiring Diagram – Mechatronic Robot 

This section describes all the **electrical connections** for the line-following and obstacle-avoidance robot using **Arduino/STM32**.

---

## **Components**

| Component              | Quantity |
|------------------------|---------|
| Microcontroller        | 1       |
| L298N Motor Driver     | 1       |
| DC Motors              | 2       |
| IR Line Sensors        | 2       |
| Ultrasonic Sensor HC-SR04 | 1    |
| Battery Pack (5V–7.4V) | 1      |

---

## **Connections**

### **1. Motors → L298N Motor Driver**

| Motor | L298N Pin |
|-------|------------|
| Left Motor  | OUT1 & OUT2 |
| Right Motor | OUT3 & OUT4 |

- Connect motor wires to the motor driver terminals.
- Ensure correct polarity for desired rotation.

---

### **2. L298N → Microcontroller**

| L298N Pin       | Microcontroller Pin |
|-----------------|------------------|
| IN1             | D5 / PWM         |
| IN2             | D6 / PWM         |
| IN3             | D9 / PWM         |
| IN4             | D10 / PWM        |
| ENA (Enable Left Motor)  | 5V / PWM optional |
| ENB (Enable Right Motor) | 5V / PWM optional |
| VCC (Motor Power)        | Battery +        |
| GND                      | Battery – / MCU GND |

> **Note:** L298N can handle higher current than Arduino/STM32 pins directly.

---

### **3. IR Line Sensors → Microcontroller**

| Sensor       | Microcontroller Pin |
|--------------|------------------|
| Left IR      | A0 (Analog Input) |
| Right IR     | A1 (Analog Input) |
| VCC          | 5V                |
| GND          | GND               |

> IR sensors detect black lines for line-following.

---

### **4. Ultrasonic Sensor HC-SR04 → Microcontroller**

| Pin  | Microcontroller Pin |
|------|------------------|
| VCC  | 5V                |
| GND  | GND               |
| TRIG | D2                 |
| ECHO | D3                 |

> Measures distance to obstacles for autonomous navigation.

---

### **5. Power Connections**

- **Battery Pack → L298N VCC & GND**  
- **L298N GND → Microcontroller GND**  
- **Microcontroller VCC → 5V regulated (if separate)**  

> Ensure **all grounds are connected** to have a common reference.

